commit_messages:
Templates

Hard-coded views have been deleted. Starting on template .html files in place of.

Reverse function

I need to revisit this topic again for better understanding.

Num Page View

Returns a view based on the index in the articles dictionary.

If user types in domain.com/first_app/(number), it returns the corresponding topic based on the dictionary index.
Finish ingredient list/Start Steps ordered list
Add recipe description. Start ingredient list
Update unordered list with Mac and Cheese link
Add paragraph describing the recipe/ Add Ingredients header and unordered list
Fix spelling mistake in file name
Add code to disable physical keyboard
Initial logic working on both screens
Add logic determined by the current screen.
Change function to look for any value for testing
Change function to look for enter key
Add toast messages to print the workzone status
Add logic to check for entry in the workzone fields
Try alternative solution for enter key
Add logic to check on manual enter press
Comment auto-enters - session profile already accomplishes this
Add timeout function to allow time for data to be entered
Add script for auto-enter on the 311 screen
Add toast to indicate script working
Added a slight delay in scan process/check the length of the workzone field
change zoneOne to check for blank instead of '*'
added logic to block the auto-enter on this screen
Removed the next screen function on a good scan - device will do that anyway
Clear the scan data on a bad scan

Update zebra_scanner.py

Added a for loop to loop through the printer dictionary

Windows Toast

added toast messages for certain conditions.
